title: Episode 214. “I’m 45 but my parents still control my money”
description: Kate and Keith have spent years afraid to spend—until now. In part 2 of this conversation, Ramit challenges them to rewrite the money scripts that have ruled their lives: Kate’s need for control, Keith’s fear of being dependent, and the invisible narratives passed down through generations. They imagine a future with travel, community, and purpose, […] Source
author: Ramit Sethi
